The players were relaxing after coming from behind to beat Croatia 2-1 at the Boleyn Ground on Wednesday, their next match will be against Portugal on Tuesday.

Meanwhile, Aguero revealed on Friday he didn't even know who Messi was the first time they met.

Speaking to City TV, he said: 'I was about to turn 17. We were both called up for some friendlies. We were at the AFA (Argentine Football Association) training complex. We were sitting at the table with him, (Ezequiel) Garay and (Mauro) Formica.

'He sat beside me. I looked at him but I didn't know him. They were talking about Nike football boots and Garay was saying that they were really good.

